      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/literature-synthesis-vr",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis modelling studies supporting model-form selection",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior published studies examining CFD-based hemolysis prediction in rotary blood pumps (covering 2008–2022) was assembled to justify the Giersiepen power-law damage accumulation model form. This synthesis aggregates findings from at least nine independent laboratory campaigns across four device platforms, demonstrating consistent predictive accuracy of the power-law approach for shear-dominated hemolysis regimes relevant to centrifugal CPB pumps. The synthesis directly informs the model-form credibility factor rationale and underpins the claim that the selected constitutive relationship is appropriate for the COU.",
      "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case"
    }
